<Base title="Morriston Trades SEO Case Study" description="How a Morriston plumbing and heating business achieved 450% organic traffic growth and 20 new leads per month through a 6-month SEO campaign in Swansea." schema={schema}>

  <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-brand mb-4">Morriston Trades Business — Organic SEO Case Study</h1>

  <div class="bg-blue-50 border-l-4 border-blue-400 p-4 rounded-r-lg my-4 text-sm text-blue-800">This case study is illustrative and based on composite data from similar local SEO campaigns. It demonstrates typical results achievable for trades and service businesses in the Morriston area.</div>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border-l-4 border-amber-400 p-4 rounded-r-lg my-6">
    <p class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-1">Quick Answer</p>
    <p class="text-gray-700">A plumbing and heating business in Morriston went from no online presence to 20 new leads per month within 6 months. The campaign achieved 450% organic traffic growth, page 1 rankings for "plumber morriston," "boiler repair swansea," and "heating engineer swansea," and a measurable return on investment from month 4 onwards.</p>
  </div>

  <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">This Morriston trades business SEO case study demonstrates what is possible when a service business with zero online visibility commits to a structured organic SEO campaign. The business was a two-person plumbing and heating operation based near Morriston Hospital, serving residential and light commercial customers across Swansea. The owner had run the business for over a decade on word of mouth alone, but referral volume was declining and younger homeowners were searching online rather than asking neighbours. The business had no website, no Google Business Profile, and no digital footprint of any kind.</p>

  <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">This case study documents the 6-month campaign that transformed the business from invisible to page 1 for its core terms, covering the challenges, the strategy, and the results. For the companion case study covering Google Maps SEO for hospitality, see the <a href="/case-studies/mumbles-restaurant-google-maps/" class="text-brand hover:underline">Mumbles restaurant case study</a>.</p>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-4">The Challenge</h2>

  <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">The business operated from premises near the Phoenix Trading Estate in Morriston, covering a service area that included Morriston, Sketty, Uplands, SA1 Waterfront, Llansamlet, and the wider Swansea postcode area. Despite being Gas Safe registered, experienced, and competitively priced, the owner had never invested in any form of online marketing. There was no website, no social media presence, and no listing on Google Maps. When a homeowner in Morriston searched for "plumber near me" or "boiler repair morriston," this business did not exist.</p>

  <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">The competitive landscape made the problem worse. Swansea has a high density of plumbing and heating businesses, many of which have invested in websites and Google Business Profiles. National aggregators like Checkatrade, MyBuilder, and Bark dominate the first page for generic trades terms, taking a commission on every lead. The business was paying indirectly through lost opportunities: every lead that went to a competitor or an aggregator was revenue that should have come direct.</p>

  <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">The owner's goals were straightforward: appear when local customers search, generate enough leads to keep two engineers busy, and stop relying on a shrinking pool of word-of-mouth referrals. The budget was modest, which meant the strategy had to be efficient and focused on the highest-impact activities first.</p>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-4">The Strategy</h2>

  <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">The campaign was structured across 6 months with a clear progression from build to optimise to expand. Every decision was guided by one question: what will generate leads fastest with the available budget?</p>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mt-8 mb-3">Months 1-2: Build the Foundation</h3>

  <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">The first step was building a website designed for conversion and SEO from the ground up. The site was built on a fast, lightweight framework with clean HTML, proper heading hierarchy, and mobile-first responsive design. Page load time was under 1.5 seconds on 4G, which is critical for trades searches where users are often on mobile dealing with an urgent problem like a burst pipe or broken boiler.</p>

  <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">The site architecture was built around service area pages. Rather than a single "Areas We Cover" page listing postcodes, we created individual pages for each target area: Morriston, Sketty, Uplands, SA1, Llansamlet, Cwmdu, and Gorseinon. Each page contained unique content about the area, the specific services offered there, typical property types and their common plumbing and heating issues, and genuine local references. The Morriston page mentioned proximity to Morriston Hospital and the residential streets surrounding the Phoenix Trading Estate. The SA1 page referenced the newer apartment developments along the waterfront and their specific heating system requirements.</p>

  <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">Simultaneously, we set up and optimised a Google Business Profile with the correct categories (Plumber, Heating Contractor, Boiler Repair Service), service area definitions matching the website, high-quality photos of completed work, and a complete service list with descriptions. We also submitted the business to 30 local directories with consistent name, address, and phone number data.</p>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mt-8 mb-3">Months 3-4: Technical SEO and Content</h3>

  <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">With the site indexed and the profile live, months 3 and 4 focused on technical optimisation and content expansion. We implemented LocalBusiness structured data with service area markup, added FAQ schema to every service page addressing common customer questions, and ensured the site passed all Core Web Vitals thresholds. Internal linking was structured so that every area page linked to relevant service pages and vice versa, creating a tight topical cluster around plumbing and heating services in Swansea.</p>

  <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">We also published practical content targeting informational queries that lead to service bookings: "How to bleed a radiator" (with a CTA for professional help if needed), "Signs your boiler needs replacing" (linking to the boiler installation service page), and "Emergency plumber Swansea: what to do before help arrives." These pages captured top-of-funnel traffic and positioned the business as a knowledgeable, trustworthy provider.</p>

  <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">The review strategy launched in month 3. Every completed job included a follow-up text with a direct link to the Google review page. The owner was coached on asking for reviews at the natural moment of satisfaction, typically when the customer expressed relief that the problem was fixed. Reviews grew steadily, each one reinforcing the business's prominence signal in Google's local algorithm.</p>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mt-8 mb-3">Months 5-6: Expansion and Refinement</h3>

  <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">By month 5, the site was ranking on page 1 for its primary terms and generating consistent leads. The focus shifted to expanding into adjacent terms and optimising conversion. We added service pages for niche offerings: power flushing, underfloor heating, smart thermostat installation, and landlord gas safety certificates. Each page targeted specific long-tail queries with lower competition but strong commercial intent.</p>

  <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">We refined the Google Business Profile with regular posts about completed projects (with customer permission), seasonal tips, and service promotions. The profile was updated with new photos monthly. We also added the business to Swansea Enterprise Park and Cwmdu Industrial Estate business directories, strengthening local entity associations in Google's knowledge graph.</p>

  <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">Conversion rate optimisation in month 6 included adding click-to-call buttons above the fold on mobile, a sticky phone number bar, and a simple quote request form. These changes increased the conversion rate from organic traffic by 35%, translating directly to more leads from the same traffic volume.</p>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-4">The Results</h2>

  <div class="grid grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-4 gap-4 my-8">
    <div class="text-center p-4 bg-gray-50 rounded-lg">
      <span class="text-3xl font-bold text-brand">450%</span>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mt-1">Organic traffic growth</p>
    </div>
    <div class="text-center p-4 bg-gray-50 rounded-lg">
      <span class="text-3xl font-bold text-brand">20</span>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mt-1">New leads per month</p>
    </div>
    <div class="text-center p-4 bg-gray-50 rounded-lg">
      <span class="text-3xl font-bold text-brand">Page 1</span>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mt-1">For primary terms</p>
    </div>
    <div class="text-center p-4 bg-gray-50 rounded-lg">
      <span class="text-3xl font-bold text-brand">6x</span>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mt-1">ROI by month 6</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">After 6 months, the business ranked on page 1 for "plumber morriston," "boiler repair swansea," "heating engineer swansea," "emergency plumber swansea," and 12 additional service-plus-location terms. Organic traffic grew by 450% from the initial baseline established in month 1. The website generated an average of 20 new leads per month through a combination of phone calls, form submissions, and Google Business Profile actions.</p>

  <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">The Google Business Profile accumulated 38 reviews with a 4.8 average rating over the campaign period. Profile views increased by over 600%, and "direction request" and "call" actions grew proportionally. The business appeared consistently in the local pack for all targeted terms within the Swansea service area.</p>

  <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">Financially, the campaign paid for itself from month 4 onwards. By month 6, the return on investment was approximately 6 to 1 based on the average job value and the conversion rate from lead to booked job. The owner was able to hire a third engineer by the end of the campaign period, directly attributable to the increase in lead volume from organic search.</p>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-4">Key Takeaways</h2>

  <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
    <li>Individual service area pages outperform a single "areas covered" page for trades businesses. Each page must contain genuinely unique content with real local references, not templated text with the area name swapped in.</li>
    <li>Mobile speed is non-negotiable for trades SEO. Customers searching for emergency plumbers or boiler repairs are on their phones and will not wait for a slow site to load.</li>
    <li>Google Business Profile and website must tell the same story. Consistent services, areas, and contact information across both signals reinforce each other in Google's ranking algorithm.</li>
    <li>Informational content drives commercial leads when structured correctly. A blog post about "signs your boiler needs replacing" captures someone at the research stage and guides them toward booking a service.</li>
    <li>Starting from zero is not a disadvantage if the foundations are built correctly. A new, well-optimised site can outrank established competitors with poorly maintained websites within 6 months.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-4">Campaign Timeline</h2>

  <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden mb-8">
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 text-sm">
      <div class="p-4 bg-gray-50 border-b md:border-b-0 md:border-r border-gray-200">
        <p class="font-semibold mb-2">Months 1-2: Build</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700">Website build, 7 service area pages, GBP setup, 30 citation submissions, mobile-first design, technical foundations</p>
      </div>
      <div class="p-4 bg-gray-50 border-b md:border-b-0 md:border-r border-gray-200">
        <p class="font-semibold mb-2">Months 3-4: Optimise</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700">Structured data, FAQ schema, informational content, review strategy launch, internal linking, Core Web Vitals</p>
      </div>
      <div class="p-4 bg-gray-50">
        <p class="font-semibold mb-2">Months 5-6: Expand</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700">Niche service pages, GBP posts and photos, local directory expansion, CRO improvements, conversion tracking</p>
