    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-4">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

  <div class="space-y-2 mb-8">
    <details class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg">
      <summary class="cursor-pointer font-medium text-gray-900 py-2 px-4">How long does SEO take for a trades business with no website?</summary>
      <div class="px-4 pb-4 text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">A trades business starting from scratch typically needs 4 to 6 months to build meaningful organic visibility. The first 2 months cover website build, Google Business Profile setup, and initial indexing. Months 3 and 4 show early ranking movement for lower-competition local terms. By months 5 and 6, the business is typically ranking on page 1 for its primary service-plus-location terms and generating consistent leads.</div>
    </details>
    <details class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg">
      <summary class="cursor-pointer font-medium text-gray-900 py-2 px-4">What SEO strategy works best for plumbers and heating engineers?</summary>
      <div class="px-4 pb-4 text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">The most effective strategy combines service area pages targeting each neighbourhood you cover, a fully optimised Google Business Profile, technical SEO for fast mobile performance, and a review generation system. Trades businesses benefit from hyper-local content because customers search for services plus their specific area, for example "plumber morriston" rather than just "plumber swansea." Each area page should contain unique, genuine content about that location.</div>
    </details>
    <details class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg">
      <summary class="cursor-pointer font-medium text-gray-900 py-2 px-4">How many leads can a trades business expect from SEO?</summary>
      <div class="px-4 pb-4 text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">A well-optimised trades business in Swansea can expect 15 to 25 new leads per month from organic search within 6 months. Lead volume depends on the range of services offered, the number of areas targeted, and seasonal demand. Plumbing and heating businesses tend to see higher lead volumes in autumn and winter, while general building and renovation trades peak in spring and summer.</div>
    </details>
    <details class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg">
      <summary class="cursor-pointer font-medium text-gray-900 py-2 px-4">Are service area pages important for trades SEO?</summary>
      <div class="px-4 pb-4 text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">Service area pages are critical for trades SEO because they match how customers search. A homeowner in Sketty searching for "boiler repair sketty" expects to find a business that explicitly serves their area. Each page should contain unique content about the area, specific services offered there, and genuine local references. Thin or duplicated area pages do more harm than good, so quality and uniqueness per page are essential.</div>
    </details>
  </div>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-4">Get Similar Results for Your Trades Business</h2>

  <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">Whether you are a plumber in Morriston, an electrician in Sketty, or a builder covering the whole of Swansea, the same organic SEO principles apply. Start with a <a href="/free-seo-audit-swansea/" class="text-brand hover:underline">free SEO audit</a> to understand your current visibility and identify the quickest wins. Review our <a href="/services/" class="text-brand hover:underline">SEO services</a>, check our <a href="/technical-seo-swansea/" class="text-brand hover:underline">technical SEO offering</a>, or browse more <a href="/case-studies/" class="text-brand hover:underline">case studies</a> to see results across different industries.</p>

